<item>
            <title>[LU-13633] kernel update [RHEL7.8 3.10.0-1127.10.1.el7]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13633</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This update fixes the following bugs:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;block mq hang of a blk_mq_freeze_queue_wait(), which waits for a zero of a q_usage_counter, which never happens (BZ#1824546)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;update qla2xxx driver with critical bug fixes (BZ#1832221)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Emulex lpfc seems to get hung up failing IOCB&apos;S continuously on kernel 3.10.0-957.21.3.el7.x86_64 leading to Oracle evictions (BZ#1835675)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Possible race between scsi_remove_device() and scsi_probe_and_add_lun() code paths. (BZ#1836890)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Hyper-V&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; hv_netvsc performance issue in HyperV 2019 (BZ#1838600)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;revert the kernel patch &quot;xfs: catch bad stripe alignment configurations&quot; (BZ#1839697)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHBA-2020:2355&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHBA-2020:2355&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
